{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPresentTheUI","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","title":"How to Present the UI","modules":[{"name":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"}]},"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI"},{"text":" ships three view modifiers that wrap RevenueCatUI’s surfaces with platform-aware presentation. Each is bound to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallState"},{"text":": presentation flags drive visibility, and the bindings dispatch matching paywall actions back through the store on dismissal. There is no local sheet state.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For platform behavior details (iOS ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fullScreenCover"},{"text":" vs macOS sheet sizing, App Store deep link on macOS), see ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/PlatformBehavior"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Before you start","anchor":"Before-you-start"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This guide assumes:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You have completed "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToImplementService","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". The plugin is registered and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"observeCustomerInfo"},{"type":"text","text":" runs on launch."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Your app target depends on the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI"},{"type":"text","text":" product:"}]}]}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":[".product(name: \"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI\", package: \"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\"),"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Step 1: Attach both sheets to a root view","anchor":"Step-1-Attach-both-sheets-to-a-root-view"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The simplest wiring uses the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"revenueCatPaywall(state:send:)"},{"text":" modifier — one call, both sheets, both dismissals:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["import SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI","","struct RootView: View {","    @Environment(AppStore.self) private var store","","    var body: some View {","        ContentView()","            .revenueCatPaywall(state: store.paywall) { action in","                store.send(.paywall(action))","            }","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The closure receives a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallAction"},{"text":" (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".dismiss"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".dismissCustomerCenter"},{"text":") and lifts it into your root action. Place the modifier on the topmost view that should host both sheets.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Step 2: Trigger the paywall from a feature","anchor":"Step-2-Trigger-the-paywall-from-a-feature"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Dispatch ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".request(reason:)"},{"text":" with a short identifier describing why you’re asking. ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallState.requestedReason"},{"text":" stores the value so the sheet (or analytics) can tailor its copy:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["Button(\"Export PDF\") {","    store.send(.paywall(.request(reason: \"export-pdf\")))","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The plugin sets ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallState.isPresented = true"},{"text":". The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"revenueCatPaywall"},{"text":" modifier observes the change and presents ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatUI.PaywallView"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Step 3: Trigger the customer center","anchor":"Step-3-Trigger-the-customer-center"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Existing subscribers manage their subscription through the customer center. Surface a button that dispatches ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".presentCustomerCenter"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["if store.paywall.isPro {","    Button(\"Manage Subscription\") {","        store.send(.paywall(.presentCustomerCenter))","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"revenueCatCustomerCenter"},{"text":" modifier presents ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatUI.CustomerCenterView"},{"text":" on iOS. On macOS it opens the system App Store subscriptions URL and immediately fires ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"onDismiss"},{"text":" (RevenueCatUI does not ship a customer center on macOS — see ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/PlatformBehavior"},{"text":").","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Step 4: Manual wiring (optional)","anchor":"Step-4-Manual-wiring-optional"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you need only one sheet, or you want to interleave other modifiers between them, attach the primitive modifiers directly. Each takes a real ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Binding<Bool>"},{"text":"; build it with a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"set:"},{"text":" that dispatches the matching dismiss action when SwiftUI clears the flag:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["ContentView()","    .revenueCatPaywall(","        isPresented: Binding(","            get: { store.paywall.isPresented },","            set: { if !$0 { store.send(.paywall(.dismiss)) } }","        )","    )","    .revenueCatCustomerCenter(","        isPresented: Binding(","            get: { store.paywall.isCustomerCenterPresented },","            set: { if !$0 { store.send(.paywall(.dismissCustomerCenter)) } }","        )","    )"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The convenience modifier ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"revenueCatPaywall(state:send:)"},{"text":" is exactly equivalent to this wiring.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Step 5: Restore from inside the paywall","anchor":"Step-5-Restore-from-inside-the-paywall"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"RevenueCatUI’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallView"},{"text":" provides its own restore button by default. If you need an additional restore affordance elsewhere (a Settings row, for example), dispatch ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".restorePurchases"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["Button(\"Restore Purchases\") {","    store.send(.paywall(.restorePurchases))","}",".disabled(store.paywall.isLoading)"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"What happens on dismiss","anchor":"What-happens-on-dismiss"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When the user dismisses the paywall, the plugin’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".dismiss"},{"text":" action clears ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallState.isPresented"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"requestedReason"},{"text":", then dispatches ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".refreshCustomerInfo"},{"text":" so the gate is reconciled — the user may have purchased while the sheet was open.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When the user dismisses the customer center, the plugin’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".dismissCustomerCenter"},{"text":" action clears ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isCustomerCenterPresented"},{"text":". No refresh is dispatched, since opening the customer center does not change entitlement state by itself; the live ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"customerInfoStream"},{"text":" from ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Step 5"},{"text":" of ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToImplementService"},{"text":" picks up any subscription change RevenueCat reports asynchronously.","type":"text"}]}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Attach the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"revenueCatPaywall"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"revenueCatCustomerCenter"},{"type":"text","text":" view modifiers from "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI"},{"type":"text","text":" to a root view, driven by "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallState"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/howtopresenttheui"]}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The matching API reference for the views described here lives in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI"},{"type":"text","text":" documentation."}],"title":"Related Documentation","anchor":"Related-Documentation","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/PlatformBehavior","doc:\/\/Swid